# GitHub Actions publishes versioned GHCR images with the repository's
# built-in GITHUB_TOKEN. No DEPLOY_* source-SSH secrets or variables are needed.
# Configure the workflow with packages: write permission.

# Server-only GHCR pull access (for private packages)
# Create a separate GitHub token with read:packages permission, then run
# `docker login ghcr.io` on the server. Do not store its value in this repository.
# Keep runtime secrets such as JWT_SECRET and LLM provider API keys only in the
# server .env; they are not GitHub Actions publishing credentials.
